ce:section.ce:para:
Preparation of Mn/CQD is illustrated in Scheme 1
                        . Briefly, Manganese acetate (2 mmol) was dissolved in toluene (12 ml). Then solution was stirred to obtain homogenous solution. Afterwards citric acid (2 ml) and urea (2 ml) were added and stirred for 15 min at room temperature. Then solution was autoclaved for 8 h at 200 centigrade degrees. Then, products were cooled in room temperature, large particles were separated by centrifuge (10,000 rpm, 15 min) and dialysis bag (0.5 kDa). Mn/CQD/SiO2 was synthesized by following method: obtained Mn/CQD (1 ml) was added to 480 ml deionized water in the present of CTAB (1 g) and NaOH (3.5 ml, 2 M). Then TEOS and APES were added to the obtained product and ultrasonic for 15 min and separated by centrifuge (70,000 rpm, 15 min). CTAB was extracted from porous silica by transferring the obtained product to ethanol for 24 h. Naproxen conjugation was performed by adding 20 mg naproxen in 15 ml DMF in the presence of DCC. Then, solution was stirred for 30 min, and 20 mg of obtained nanoparticles were added into solution. After 24 stirring the product was purified by centrifuge and then lyophilized (Scheme 2
                        ).

The morphology and size of the synthesized Mn/CQD/SiO2 was investigated by scanning electron microscopy (SEM) analysis and is presented in Fig. 3
                     a. As can be seen, quasi-spherical morphology and regular size (with about 25–40 nm) is observed from the SEM images. In addition, SEM image showed aggregation in some areas. Transmission electron microscopy (TEM) was used to observe the distribution of the Mn/CQD/SiO2, as showed in Fig. 3b. The Mn/CQD/SiO2 is composed of nanoparticles with regular and homogeneous morphology with average particle size of 35 nm. Energy-dispersive X-ray spectroscopy (EDS) elemental mapping of the Mn/CQD/SiO2 product also describes the space distribution of Mn, C, Si and O in individual tetrahedrons (Fig. 3c). The EDs mapping showed that the four elements were evenly distributed in the structure of sample. DLS was performed to determine the size and zeta potential of Mn/CQD/SiO2 were approximately 70 nm and −20 mV presented in (Fig. 4
                     ).
